main event: Three solid, brightly lit, circular objects were observed in the sky over Cleveland, Ohio on August 28, 1964 at approximately 2115 hours.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be solid and brightly lit.
The objects were silent and traveled at a high rate of speed.
The objects were observed for approximately 2 to 3 minutes before disappearing from view.
The report includes a handwritten form with a diagram or sketch labeled 'FLYING SAUCERS FROM OUTER SPACE'.
The report is from an appendix or technical information sheet related to Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program to investigate unidentified flying objects (UFOs).
sighted object: Three solid, brightly lit, circular objects
